places.placeDescription: A terrestrial rocky planet covered with oceans and a wide variety of life.
places.inhabitantsDescription: Relatively intelligent bipedal mammals capable of contemplating their own death. Addicted to coffee and afternoon naps. Has a masochistic relationship with programming.

places.placeDescription: Ancestral home of House Stark, capital of and seat of power in the north.
places.inhabitantsDescription: Hardy and rugged folk who enjoy winter sports and sunburn very severely and quickly.

places.location: An archipelago splitting the North Sea and Great Sea. One of the Northern Kingdoms west of Temeria.
places.placeDescription: A harsh, cold, windy and mountainous chain of islands.
places.inhabitantsDescription: Hardworking and determined people who aren't particularly polite or sophisticated but who have their own sort of rough charm.

places.location: Officially in an unknown state in the USA
places.placeDescription: A satirically typical middle-American town that's a cross between an unremarkable middle-sized city and random cookie-cutter suburbia.
places.inhabitantsDescription: Yellow, humanoid and presumably mammalian, typically characterized by having four fingers

places.placeDescription: Mordor; is the realm and base of the evil Sauron. It lay to the east of Gondor and the great river Anduin, and to the south of Mirkwood.
places.inhabitantsDescription: Orc created from mud and very ugly creatures. They are useful in war has no value to no one.

places.location: Orbit of the Saturn, Solar System, Milky Way Galaxy
places.placeDescription: Cooper station is a conical `o neill cylinder` structure hanging of the Saturn`s orbit. It is close to a wormhole and it is a refugee camp for Earth humans.
places.inhabitantsDescription: After nearly extintion of life on Earth, humans escaped from Earth and settled in the Cooper Station.

places.location: Several weeks of spaceflight from the Wormhole near by Saturn.
places.placeDescription: Gargantua is a very massive, rapidly spinning black hole. Used for slingshots by Nasa astronauts.
places.inhabitantsDescription: By calculations of Kip Thorne, Gargantua is about 100 million solar masses, placing it firmly as a supermassive black hole. No life forms could survive inside of this black hole .

places.placeDescription: The land was known as 'Rohan' to the Men of Gondor, and its people the Rohirrim, meaning 'the Horse-lords', but the people of Rohan called themselves the Eorlingas, sons of Eorl the Young, first King of Rohan.
places.inhabitantsDescription: They are proud and willful, but they are true-hearted, generous in thought and deed; bold but not cruel; wise but unlearned, writing no books but singing many songs, after the manner of the children of Men before the Dark Years.

places.placeDescription: The political and financial capital of Japan, whose metropolitan population is nearly 50 million people. It has approximately 900 train and subway stations and nearly 40 millions passengers daily.
places.inhabitantsDescription: An island people known as the 'Japanese' whose culture and society mostly developed in isolation.

places.placeDescription: Part of a binary star system, the planet orbited two scorching suns, resulting in the world lacking the necessary surface water to sustain large populations. As a result, many residents of the planet instead drew water from the atmosphere via moisture farms.
places.inhabitantsDescription: Jawas were a sentient species of meter-tall furry humanoids native to the Outer Rim desert world of Tatooine. Jawas who migrated from Tatooine were referred to as Offworld Jawas.
